sentences: Gottlieb was born on January 28, 1917 in the Canarsie neighborhood of Brooklyn, and grew up in Bound Brook, New Jersey, where his father was in the building and lumber business.
He graduated from Lehigh University in 1938 with a degree in economics.
Gottlieb was drafted into the Army Air Corps in 1943, and  served as a photography and a classifications officer.
In 1948, Gottlieb retired from jazz journalism in order to spend more time with his wife, Delia, and children.
Gottlieb died of complications of a stroke on April 23, 2006 in Great Neck, New York.

sentences: William Paul Gottlieb (January 28, 1917 – April 23, 2006) was an American photographer and newspaper columnist who is best known for his classic photographs of the leading performers of the Golden Age of American jazz in the 1930s and 1940s.
In his last year of college, he began writing a weekly jazz column for The Washington Post.
He worked as a writer-photographer for Down Beat magazine, and his work also appeared frequently in Record Changer, the Saturday Review, and Collier's.
